{"sections":[],"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"content","content":[{"type":"heading","text":"Overview","anchor":"Overview","level":2},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Use ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"https:\/\/daringfireball.net\/projects\/markdown\/syntax","type":"reference"},{"text":", a","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"lightweight markup language, to give structure and style to your documentation.","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"DocC includes a custom dialect of Markdown, documentation markup, which"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"extends Markdown’s syntax to include features like symbol linking, improved","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"image support, term lists, and asides.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"To ensure consistent structure and styling, use DocC’s documentation markup for"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"all of the documentation you write.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"level":3,"text":"Add a Page Title and Section Headers","type":"heading","anchor":"Add-a-Page-Title-and-Section-Headers"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"To add a page title, precede the text you want to use with a hash ("},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"#"},{"type":"text","text":") and a"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"space. For the page title of an article or API collection, use plain text only."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"syntax":"markdown","type":"codeListing","code":["# Getting Started with Sloths"]},{"name":"Important","type":"aside","style":"important","content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Page titles must be the first line of content in a documentation","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"file. One or more empty lines can precede the page title.","type":"text"}]}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"For the page title of a landing page, enter a symbol link by wrapping the framework’s"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"module name within a set of double backticks (``)."}]},{"syntax":"markdown","code":["# ``SlothCreator``"],"type":"codeListing"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"For a documentation extension file, enter a symbol link by wrapping the path to the symbol","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"within double backticks (``). The path may start with the framework’s module name","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"or with the name of a top-level symbol in the module."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"The following example shows a documentation extension link starting with a framework module name:","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"codeListing","code":["# ``SlothCreator\/CareSchedule\/Event``"],"syntax":"markdown"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The following example shows a documentation extension link to the same symbol starting with a top-level symbol name:"}]},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"markdown","code":["# ``CareSchedule\/Event``"]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Augment every page title with a short and concise single-sentence abstract or"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"summary that provides additional information about the content. Add the summary","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"using a new paragraph directly below the page title."}]},{"code":["# Getting Started with Sloths","","Create a sloth and assign personality traits and abilities."],"type":"codeListing","syntax":"markdown"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"To add a header for an Overview or a Discussion section, use a double hash"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"(","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"##"},{"type":"text","text":") and a space, and then include either term in plain text."}]},{"syntax":"markdown","code":["## Overview"],"type":"codeListing"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"For all other section headers, use a triple hash ("},{"code":"###","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":") and a space, and then","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"add the title of the header in plain text."}]},{"syntax":"markdown","code":["### Create a Sloth"],"type":"codeListing"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Use this type of section header in framework landing pages, top-level pages,","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"articles, and occasionally in symbol reference pages where you need to"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"provide more detail."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"anchor":"Format-Text-in-Bold-Italics-and-Code-Voice","text":"Format Text in Bold, Italics, and Code Voice","type":"heading","level":3},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"DocC provides three ways to format the text in your documentation. You can","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"apply bold or italic styling, or you can use code voice, which renders the"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"specified text in a monospace font.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"To add bold styling, wrap the text in a pair of double asterisks ("},{"code":"**","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":").","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"Alternatively, use double underscores (","type":"text"},{"code":"__","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":")."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"The following example uses bold styling for the names of the sloths:","type":"text"}]},{"syntax":"markdown","code":["**Super Sloth**: Likes to eat sticks.","__Silly Sloth__: Prefers twigs for breakfast."],"type":"codeListing"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Use italicized text to introduce new or alternative terms to the reader. To add"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"italic styling, wrap the text in a set of single underscores (","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"_"},{"type":"text","text":") or single"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"asterisks (","type":"text"},{"code":"*","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":")."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The following example uses italics for the words "},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"metabolism"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"type":"text","text":" and "},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"habitat"}]},{"text":":","type":"text"}]},{"type":"codeListing","code":["A sloth's _metabolism_ is highly dependent on its *habitat*."],"syntax":"markdown"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Use code voice to refer to symbols inline, or to include short code fragments,"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"such as class names or method signatures.  To add code voice, wrap the text in"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"a set of backticks (`).","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"In the following example, DocC renders the words "},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"ice"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"text":", ","type":"text"},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"text":"fire","type":"text"}]},{"type":"text","text":", "},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"wind"}]},{"type":"text","text":", and"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"lightning"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"text":" in a monospace font:","type":"text"}]},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"markdown","code":["If your sloth possesses one of the special powers: `ice`, `fire`, ","`wind`, or `lightning`."]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"To include multiple lines of code, use a code listing instead. For more"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"information, see "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.docc\/documentation\/docc\/formatting-your-documentation-content#Add-Code-Listings","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":"."}],"type":"paragraph"}],"name":"Note","type":"aside","style":"note"},{"anchor":"Add-Code-Listings","text":"Add Code Listings","level":3,"type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"DocC includes support for code listings, or fenced code blocks, which allow you"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"to go beyond the basic declaration sections you find in symbol reference pages,"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"and to provide more complete code examples for adopters of your framework. You can","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"include code listings in your in-source symbol documentation, in extension"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"files, and in articles and tutorials."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"To create a code listing, start a new paragraph and add three backticks"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"(```). Then, directly following the backticks, add the name of the","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"programming language in lowercase text. Add one or more lines of code, and then","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"add a new line and terminate the code listing by adding another three backticks:","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"syntax":"markdown","code":["```swift","struct Sightseeing: Activity {","    func perform(with sloth: inout Sloth) -> Speed {","        sloth.energyLevel -= 10","        return .slow","    }","}","```"],"type":"codeListing"},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"When formatting your code listing, use spaces to indent lines","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"instead of tabs so that DocC preserves the indentation when compiling your"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"documentation.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}],"name":"Important","type":"aside","style":"important"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"DocC uses the programming language you specify to apply the correct syntax"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"color formatting. For the example above, DocC generates the following:"}]},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift","code":["struct Sightseeing: Activity {","    func perform(with sloth: inout Sloth) -> Speed {","        sloth.energyLevel -= 10","        return .slow","    }","}"]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The following table lists the names of the programming languages you can specify"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"to enable syntax highlighting for a particular code listing. Each language may"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"have one or more aliases.","type":"text"}]},{"header":"row","rows":[[[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Name"}]}],[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Aliases","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]],[[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"bash","type":"text"}]}],[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"sh, zsh","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]],[[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"c"}],"type":"paragraph"}],[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"h"}],"type":"paragraph"}]],[[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"cpp","type":"text"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"cc, c++, h++, hpp, hh, hxx, cxx","type":"text"}]}]],[[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"css","type":"text"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[]}]],[[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"diff"}],"type":"paragraph"}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"patch"}]}]],[[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"http"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"https"}]}]],[[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"java"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"jsp","type":"text"}]}]],[[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"javascript"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"js, jsx, mjs, cjs","type":"text"}]}]],[[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"json"}],"type":"paragraph"}],[{"inlineContent":[],"type":"paragraph"}]],[[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"llvm","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[]}]],[[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"markdown","type":"text"}]}],[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"md, mkdown, mkd","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]],[[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"objective-c","type":"text"}]}],[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"mm, objc, obj-c, objectivec"}],"type":"paragraph"}]],[[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"perl","type":"text"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"pl, pm","type":"text"}]}]],[[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"php"}],"type":"paragraph"}],[{"inlineContent":[],"type":"paragraph"}]],[[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"python"}],"type":"paragraph"}],[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"py, gyp, ipython"}],"type":"paragraph"}]],[[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"ruby"}],"type":"paragraph"}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"rb, gemspec, podspec, thor, irb","type":"text"}]}]],[[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"scss"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[]}]],[[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"shell","type":"text"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"console, shellsession","type":"text"}]}]],[[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"swift"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[]}]],[[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"xml","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}],[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"html, xhtml, rss, atom, xjb, xsd, xsl, plist, wsf, svg","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]]],"type":"table"},{"anchor":"Add-Bulleted-Numbered-and-Term-Lists","text":"Add Bulleted, Numbered, and Term Lists","type":"heading","level":3},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"DocC supports the following list types:","type":"text"}]},{"rows":[[[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Type","type":"text"}]}],[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Usage"}],"type":"paragraph"}]],[[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Bulleted list","type":"text"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Groups items that can appear in any order."}]}]],[[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Numbered list","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Delineates a sequence of events in a particular order."}]}]],[[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Term list"}],"type":"paragraph"}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Defines a series of term-definition pairs."}]}]]],"type":"table","header":"row"},{"name":"Important","style":"important","content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Don’t add images or code listings between list items. Bulleted and"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"numbered lists must contain two or more items.","type":"text"}]}],"type":"aside"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"To create a bulleted list, precede each of the list’s items with an asterisk (","type":"text"},{"code":"*","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":") and a","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"space. Alternatively, use a dash ("},{"code":"-","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":") or a plus sign (","type":"text"},{"code":"+","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":") instead of an asterisk (","type":"text"},{"code":"*","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":"); the list markers are interchangeable."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"syntax":"markdown","code":["* Ice","- Fire","* Wind","+ Lightning"],"type":"codeListing"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"To create a numbered list, precede each of the list’s items with the number of the step, then a period (","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"."},{"text":") and a space.","type":"text"}]},{"syntax":"markdown","type":"codeListing","code":["1. Give the sloth some food.","2. Take the sloth for a walk.","3. Read the sloth a story.","4. Put the sloth to bed."]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"To create a term list, precede each term with a dash ("},{"code":"-","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":") and a","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"space, the "},{"code":"term","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" keyword, and another space. Then add a colon ("},{"code":":","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":"), a space, and the definition after the term."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"code":["- term Ice: Ice sloths thrive below freezing temperatures.","- term Fire: Fire sloths thrive at boiling temperatures.","- term Wind: Wind sloths thrive at soaring altitudes.","- term Lightning: Lightning sloths thrive in stormy climates."],"type":"codeListing","syntax":"markdown"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"A list item’s text, including terms and their definitions, can use the same","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"style attributes as other text, and include links to other content, including"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"symbols."}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/org.swift.docc\/documentation\/docc"]]},"kind":"article","abstract":[{"text":"Enhance your content’s presentation with special formatting and styling for text and lists.","type":"text"}],"seeAlsoSections":[{"anchor":"Structure-and-Formatting","generated":true,"title":"Structure and Formatting","identifiers":["doc:\/\/org.swift.docc\/documentation\/docc\/adding-tables-of-data","doc:\/\/org.swift.docc\/documentation\/docc\/other-formatting-options","doc:\/\/org.swift.docc\/documentation\/docc\/adding-images","doc:\/\/org.swift.docc\/documentation\/docc\/adding-structure-to-your-documentation-pages","doc:\/\/org.swift.docc\/documentation\/docc\/customizing-the-appearance-of-your-documentation-pages"]}],"schemaVersion":{"patch":0,"major":0,"minor":3},"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/docc\/formatting-your-documentation-content"]}],"metadata":{"roleHeading":"Article","role":"article","modules":[{"name":"DocC"}],"title":"Formatting Your Documentation Content"},"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/org.swift.docc\/documentation\/docc\/formatting-your-documentation-content","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"references":{"doc://org.swift.docc/documentation/docc":{"url":"\/documentation\/docc","kind":"symbol","type":"topic","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Produce rich API reference documentation and interactive tutorials for your Swift framework or package."}],"title":"DocC","role":"collection","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.docc\/documentation\/docc"},"doc://org.swift.docc/documentation/docc/adding-structure-to-your-documentation-pages":{"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.docc\/documentation\/docc\/adding-structure-to-your-documentation-pages","url":"\/documentation\/docc\/adding-structure-to-your-documentation-pages","title":"Adding Structure to Your Documentation Pages","role":"article","type":"topic","kind":"article","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Make symbols easier to find by arranging them into groups and collections."}]},"doc://org.swift.docc/documentation/docc/other-formatting-options":{"url":"\/documentation\/docc\/other-formatting-options","type":"topic","role":"article","title":"Other Formatting Options","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Improve the presentation and structure of your content by incorporating special page elements."}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.docc\/documentation\/docc\/other-formatting-options","kind":"article"},"doc://org.swift.docc/documentation/docc/formatting-your-documentation-content#Add-Code-Listings":{"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.docc\/documentation\/docc\/formatting-your-documentation-content#Add-Code-Listings","type":"topic","title":"Add Code Listings","url":"\/documentation\/docc\/formatting-your-documentation-content#Add-Code-Listings","abstract":[],"kind":"section"},"doc://org.swift.docc/documentation/docc/customizing-the-appearance-of-your-documentation-pages":{"url":"\/documentation\/docc\/customizing-the-appearance-of-your-documentation-pages","type":"topic","role":"article","title":"Customizing the Appearance of Your Documentation Pages","abstract":[{"text":"Customize the look and feel of your documentation webpages.","type":"text"}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.docc\/documentation\/docc\/customizing-the-appearance-of-your-documentation-pages","kind":"article"},"doc://org.swift.docc/documentation/docc/adding-tables-of-data":{"type":"topic","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Arrange information into rows and columns."}],"role":"article","kind":"article","title":"Adding Tables of Data","url":"\/documentation\/docc\/adding-tables-of-data","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.docc\/documentation\/docc\/adding-tables-of-data"},"doc://org.swift.docc/documentation/docc/adding-images":{"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.docc\/documentation\/docc\/adding-images","url":"\/documentation\/docc\/adding-images","title":"Adding Images to Your Content","role":"article","type":"topic","kind":"article","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Elevate your content’s visual appeal by adding images."}]},"https://daringfireball.net/projects/markdown/syntax":{"identifier":"https:\/\/daringfireball.net\/projects\/markdown\/syntax","type":"link","title":"Markdown","titleInlineContent":[{"text":"Markdown","type":"text"}],"url":"https:\/\/daringfireball.net\/projects\/markdown\/syntax"}}}